        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 6:36PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 636 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles north of Kannapolis, or over Landis, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kannapolis, Salisbury, China Grove, Landis, Enochville, Mount Ulla,
and Piedmont Research Station.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
